			<div class="post-details-content">
				<div class="single-post-section-header">Article Details<a href="https://growthhackers.com/login/?redirect_to=https%3A%2F%2Fgrowthhackers.com%2Ffrom-minimum-viable-course-to-100000-users%2F" class="show-editor-login" title="Log In to Edit" style="display: none;">Log in to edit</a></div><div class="single-post-details"><p>Conrad Wadowski, co-founder of Fedora, tells the story of Bitfountain, one of the early successes on the Fedora platform. Bitfountain, which offers instructional courses on programming, started off as a side project but now has over 100,000 people on its mailing list and generated revenues over $2 million.</p>
